  {
    "model": "blog.post",
    "pk": 11,
    "fields": {
      "title": "The Thrilling Showdown in Miami",
      "slug": "the-thrilling-showdown-in-miami",
      "excerpt": "",
      "content": "Played at Miami Stadium, the knockout match was an instant classic. The reigning champions expected a straightforward advance, but Cabo Verde came armed with defensive discipline and a 10-save heroic performance from 40-year-old goalkeeper Vozinha.The Opener: Lionel Messi broke the deadlock with a brilliant strike, marking his record-extending 20th career World Cup goal.The Resilience: Cabo Verde refused to back down. Deroy Duarte capitalized on a defensive lapse to level the match at 1-1, stunning the crowd in Miami Stadium.Extra-time Drama: Lisandro Martďż˝nez restored Argentina's lead in the 103rd minute, but Sidny Lopes Cabral responded almost immediately to equalize again.The Winner: Just when it seemed Cabo Verde was heading for a historic upset, championship grit carried Argentina through.",
